  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "What are the best online sites to prepare for gate(EE)?",
  "response": "Preparing for the GATE (Graduate Aptitude Test in Engineering) in Electrical Engineering (EE) requires a robust study plan and access to quality resources. Here are some of the best online platforms to help you prepare:\n\n1. **NPTEL (National Programme on Technology Enhanced Learning)**: This initiative by Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs) and Indian Institute of Science (IISc) offers free online courses. The video lectures can be helpful for understanding core concepts.\n\n2. **Unacademy**: This platform offers comprehensive courses and live classes specifically tailored for GATE preparation, including personalized mentorship from top educators.\n\n3. **Gradeup (now BYJU\u2019S Exam Prep)**: Their app and website provide GATE-related quizzes, mock tests, and study materials. The app features a user-friendly interface where you can interact with peers and educators.\n\n4. **Made Easy Prime**: They offer detailed online lectures, live doubt sessions, and test series which are valuable for GATE aspirants. Made Easy has long been known for quality coaching in GATE.\n\n5. **GATE Academy**: Known for their structured online courses and study materials, they provide video lectures, test series, and doubt-solving sessions.\n\n6. **GATE Forum**: Offers online classes, test series, and study materials. They also have an app for learning on the go.\n\n7. **Study Tonight**: Although primarily focused on computer science topics, Study Tonight also features several resources related to GATE preparations.\n\n8. **Coursera and edX**: Not specifically for GATE, but you can find courses that help strengthen your fundamental concepts in electrical engineering.\n\n9. **Testbook**: Offers a wide array of test series specific to GATE along with study resources and analysis to help you focus on key areas.\n\n10. **Khan Academy**: While not GATE-specific, Khan Academy offers excellent resources for mastering fundamental concepts in mathematics and certain engineering topics.\n\n11. **YouTube**: Channels like 'Neso Academy', 'GATE Lectures by Ravindrababu Ravula', and others offer free and comprehensive video lectures on various topics related to electrical engineering.\n\nIt's important to choose the resources that best fit your learning style and to combine these online platforms with good textbooks and consistent practice with previous years' question papers.",
